article.headline: Ball St. 69, IPFW 62
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Peyton Stovall shot 14-of-17 from the free-throw line and scored 37 points to help Ball State to its first win of the season Monday, a 69-62 victory over IPFW. The Cardinals (1-11) scored 26 points off free throws while being outscored from the field. IPFW (5-8) managed just 10 points from the free-throw line but shot 22-of-52 from the field and 8-of-17 from 3-point range. Ball State shot 20-of-48 on field goals and 3-of-10 from beyond the arc. Ball State beat the Mastodons 31-28 off the glass and scored 21 points off turnovers. Stovall shot 10-of-16 from the field and made 3-of-4 3-pointers. He also had nine rebounds. Anthony Newell had 18 points for the Cardinals, who never trailed and led 35-20 at halftime. David Carson led IPFW with 17 points.
